    "actor_description": "It lands-clean. For a second I'm not thinking, I'm feeling: heat in my chest, a sharp lift behind the ribs, the sudden lightness of pressure coming off. My shoulders drop like they were braced against something I stopped noticing. A laugh tries to get out; so does a shout. I taste salt and breath and the aftershock of effort, but underneath it is simple certainty: we won. I did that. The last few minutes rearrange themselves into something that was worth the strain.",
    "description_text": "{actor} breaks open-tension giving way to a grin they don't bother to hide. Their posture expands, chest up, limbs looser, like a band snapped and the body remembered it has space. A sound escapes them-laughter, a shout, a sharp exhale that's half victory and half relief.",
    "alternate_descriptions": {
        "auditory": "I hear a bright burst-laughter or a single victorious noise-followed by an exhale that sounds like pressure venting.",
        "tactile": "A nearby presence suddenly gets bigger-energy spilling outward, movements wide and unguarded.",
        "olfactory": "Warm breath and the salt of exertion drift by, but the acrid edge of stress is gone-lighter air, cleaner sweat."
